## Cron / Loop Setup

Sprint-mode runs via a background bash loop. The interval is configurable.

```bash
# sprint-cron.sh — injects /sprint-mode at configured interval
# Run: nohup bash ${ACG_ROOT}/tools/sprint-cron.sh > /tmp/sprint-cron.log 2>&1 &
INTERVAL=1800  # seconds (30 min) — adjust as needed
while true; do
  sleep "$INTERVAL"
  # Find the active ACG primary pane
  PANE=$(tmux list-panes -a -F '#{pane_id} #{session_name}' | grep 'acg-primary\|acg_primary' | head -1 | awk '{print $1}')
  if [ -z "$PANE" ]; then
    # Fallback: any pane with 'acg' in session name
    PANE=$(tmux list-panes -a -F '#{pane_id} #{session_name}' | grep 'acg' | head -1 | awk '{print $1}')
  fi
  if [ -n "$PANE" ]; then
    tmux send-keys -t "$PANE" '/sprint-mode' Enter
  fi
done
```

**To start**: `nohup bash ${ACG_ROOT}/tools/sprint-cron.sh > /tmp/sprint-cron.log 2>&1 &`
**To stop**: `pkill -f sprint-cron.sh`

The existing `autonomy_nudge.sh` cron handles full BOOPs. Sprint-mode loop is a
separate process for manned build sprints only.

